Antenna (
Fig. 4 E
): Total length 193–198 µm long, about 0.61 times as long as head. 7 –segmented, each segment length (in µm): 75 –80, 78; 13 –17, 15; 28 –30, 29; 23 –25, 24; 15 –15, 15; 4 ; 3 . AR = 0.80–0.83 , 0.81 . Basal segment 28 –32, 30 µm wide, ratio (L/W): 2.46–2.58 , 2.52 . Ring organ located 2 / 3 of basal segment, 6 –7, 7 µm in diameter, distance from base 50 –55, 54 µm long. Second antennal segment relatively short, about as long as wide (width: 12.5 –15, 13 µm). Segment 2 ratio (L/W): 0.83–1.2 , 0.96 . Blade situated at 2 / 3 of third segment, 45 µm long, extending to base of sixth segment. Accessory blade on apex of third segment, 7.5 –10, 8 µm long, not reaching middle part of 4 th segment. Style located at apex of fifth segment, about as long as sixth segment.

Labrum: SI hair­like, small. SII simple and strong, blade­like. SIV divided into 3 segments, each segment length (in µm) 13, 12, 7.5 ( n = 1 ). Premandible (
Fig. 4 F
