Mandible (
Fig. 4 G
): Total length 112–118, 116 m long. With 1 apical tooth and two sharp inner teeth. Apical tooth 25 µm long, combined width of two inner teeth 13–15 µm, only about 1 / 2 length of apical tooth. Seta subdentalis 6 –8, 7 m long. Seta interna with three long blade­like branches. Pecten mandibularis with 2–3 short branches, which do not extend beyond inner margin.

Maxilla (
Fig. 4 H
): Maxillary palp with basal segment about 3 times as long as wide (length 45–52 µm; width 16–18 µm). Ring organ located in middle. Distal part with 4–6 short blades, b sensillum with ratio of basal segment to distal part about 6 : 1 .
